                            <time datetime="2014-03-29">March 29, 2014 at 5:58 pm</time>
                        </a>
                                            </span>
                                    </div>

                <div class="comment-text">
                    <p>Thank you for this article. I think it&#8217;s only incidental that co-ops tend to be local enterprises. I think the much bigger aspect is the ownership. </p>
<p>All profit on capital is paid at the point of ownership, i.e. to the owner. When &#8220;employees&#8221; own the capital (the &#8220;means of production&#8221; as we have heard it famously called), then profit must come to them. I recommend the work of Marjorie Kelly for a large treatment of cooperative ownership and how successful (and prevalent) it actually is in this world.</p>
                </div>
